dium with' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'your written explanation.  The person or entity that provided you with' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'the defective work may elect to provide a replacement copy in lieu of a' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'refund.  If you received the work electronically, the person or entity' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'providing it to you may choose to give you a second opportunity to' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'receive the work electronically in lieu of a refund.  If the second copy' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'is also defective, you may demand a refund in writing without further' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'opportunities to fix the problem.' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'1.F.4.  Except for the limited right of replacement or refund set forth' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'in paragraph 1.F.3, this work is provided to you ''AS-IS'' WITH NO OTHER' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTIBILITY OR FITNESS FOR ANY PURPOSE.' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'1.F.5.  Some states do not allow disclaimers of certain implied' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'warranties or the exclusion or limitation of certain types of damages.' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'If any disclaimer or limitation set forth in this agreement violates the' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'law of the state applicable to this agreement, the agreement shall be' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'interpreted to make the maximum disclaimer or limitation permitted by' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'the applicable state law.  The invalidity or unenforceability of any' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'provision of this agreement shall not void the remaining provisions.' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) + N'' + NCHAR(13) + N'' + NCHAR(10) +